# ===========================
# MonsterASP / Deployment
# ===========================

# Don't commit deployment artifacts
artifacts/
site66264.PublishSettings
*.publishsettings

# Keep deployment scripts, but ignore sensitive configs
# Keep: .deployment
# Keep: deploy.cmd
# Keep: web.config (with placeholder values only!)

# ===========================
# Documentation (Optional)
# ===========================

# Uncomment if you don't want to commit these:
# IMPLEMENTATION_SUMMARY.md
# DEPLOYMENT_CHECKLIST.md
# MONSTERASP_DEPLOYMENT_GUIDE.md
# QUICK_DEPLOY_MONSTERASP.md
# GITHUB_DEPLOY_SETUP.md

# ===========================
# IMPORTANT: What TO Commit
# ===========================

# ✅ DO commit:
# - Source code (*.cs, *.tsx, *.ts, *.js)
# - Project files (*.csproj, *.slnx, package.json)
# - Deployment scripts (.deployment, deploy.cmd)
# - web.config (ONLY with placeholder values, NO real secrets!)
# - Migrations folder (ClientSphere.Infrastructure/Migrations/)
# - Documentation files (*.md)
# - .gitignore itself

# ❌ NEVER commit:
# - .env files with real secrets
# - appsettings.json with real connection strings (use placeholders)
# - node_modules/
# - bin/ or obj/ folders
# - publish/ folder
# - dist/ folder
# - *.user files
# - SSL certificates
# - Personal access tokens
# - Passwords or API keys

# ===========================
# Verification Commands
# ===========================

# Check what will be committed:
# git status

# Check what's being ignored:
# git check-ignore -v <filename>

# Remove accidentally committed sensitive files:
# git rm --cached <filename>
# git commit -m "Remove sensitive file"
appsettings*.json
